 challenge ===\nClassmate launched a program called ''Classmate Ideas for India challenge''.<ref>[http://www.classmateideasforindia.com/ Classmate Ideas for India challenge] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100904145757/http://www.classmateideasforindia.com/ |date=2010-09-04 }}</ref> This was a part of the company's centenary initiative.<ref name=\"autogenerated6\">{{cite web |url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/news-by-industry/cons-products/tobacco/ITC-Leading-Multi-business-conglomerate-turns-100/articleshow/6423526.cms?curpg=2 |title=ITC: Leading Multi-business conglomerate turns 100 |date=2010-08-24 |publisher=[[The Economic Times]]}}</ref> The nationwide program would invite ideas of the youth who have the potential to transform India. Classmate Ideas for India challenge plans to reach out to 2.5 million students across 30 cities, 500 schools and 200 colleges across the country.<ref name=\"autogenerated7\">{{cite web |url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/2010/08/24/stories/2010082451200200.htm |title=ITC launches Classmate Ideas challenge |date=2010-08-23 |publisher=[[Business Line]]}}</ref> The CII-ITC Centre of Excellence for Sustainable Development, [[World Wide Fund for Nature|WWF]] India, the Tony Blair Faith Foundation, Janaagraha and the Akshaya Patra Foundation among others are the program partners for the event.<ref name=\"autogenerated13\">{{cite web |url=http://www.afaqs.com/media/story.html?sid=28264_ITC+announces+Classmate+Ideas+for+India+Challenge |title=\nITC announces Classmate Ideas for India Challenge |date=2010-09-15 |publisher=afaqs}}</ref> The program will encourage the finalists with an internship with relevant program partners, besides cash prizes and other rewards. Additionally, the top five winners would be sent to a one-week international study tour.<ref name=\"autogenerated10\">{{cite web |url=http://www.indiainfoline.com/Markets/News/ITCs-Classmate-announces-Classmate-Ideas-for-India-Challenge/4913283067 |t